metadata.title: Spotted Seals  (Phoca largha) in Alaska

creators.name: Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Marine Fisheries Service (NMFS), Alaska Fisheries Science Center (AFSC), National Marine Mammal Laboratory (NMML)

metadata.description: Aerial surveys were flown in spring and summer (April, June and August 1992;  September  1993) along the West Coast of Alaska from Cape Newenham to Pt Barrow, including Nunivak and St. Lawrence Islands.
metadata.notes:
Purpose: To count hauled out seals on coastal areas of western Alaska north of Bristol Bay
